    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "here's the text from that section:\n\n\"4.2 Price Adjustments: SwiftRoute shall maintain fixed fuel rates for the duration of the standard term. However, during peak demand periods (defined as Q3 and Q4), the Supplier reserves the right to implement rate adjustments of up to 5% to account for market volatility. Such adjustments shall be communicated to SwiftRoute via electronic notice 7 days prior to the effective date.\"\n\ndoes that mean they can just hike the prices on us without a formal signed amendment or anything? i really need to know if we're protected here.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
